main event: On 22 September 1956 at 0107Z, an object the size and shape of a weather balloon, white in color, was observed on course 270 degrees top to bottom with no radar contact. The observer believed it to be an astro body, possibly a balloon. The case was evaluated as after Capella.
interesting points: The sighting lasted for a continuous period of time.
The object was observed to be white in color and similar in size and shape to a weather balloon.
There was no radar contact with the object.
The observer believed it to be a astro body, possibly a balloon.
The case was evaluated and categorized under different possibilities including 'Possibly Balloon' and 'Possibly Astronomical'.
sighted object: White object similar in size and shape to a weather balloon
